review_blob: Has a nice pour that is golden in color with a white head. Has a fruity hoppy nose. Had a smooth hoppy bite that is not over powering with a nice finish

Opening the bottle the aroma was quite complex. It had a nutty, caramel toasty smell but also had an off smell and was almost apprehensive in even drinking it. I poured it into a glass and it had a dark amber with an off white head to it. When I had a taste though it was surprisingly good. It was mellow but mildly bitter with a somewhat sweet aftertaste
On opening the bottle has a nice smell of banana bread. Has a nice golden color and pours nice Very nice taste with a hint of bananas.
